.TH TEAMS-EXAMPLES 7 "May 26, 2026" "teams-cli 0.2.3" "Miscellaneous Information"
.SH NAME
teams-examples \- practical examples for the teams CLI
.SH DESCRIPTION
This page contains copyable examples for common
.B teams
workflows. Replace placeholder IDs before running write commands.
.SH LOGIN
.nf
teams auth login --device-code
teams auth doctor --output json
teams auth status --output json
.fi
.SH DISCOVER TEAM AND CHANNEL IDS
.nf
TEAM_ID=$(teams team list --output json | jq -r '.data[] | select(.displayName=="Engineering") | .id')
CHANNEL_ID=$(teams channel list "$TEAM_ID" --output json | jq -r '.data[] | select(.displayName=="General") | .id')
.fi
.SH SEND A CHANNEL MESSAGE
.nf
teams message send \\
  --team "$TEAM_ID" \\
  --channel "$CHANNEL_ID" \\
  --body "Release 2.4.1 is deployed." \\
  --output json
.fi
.SH SEND A CHAT MESSAGE
.nf
teams message send \\
  --chat "$CHAT_ID" \\
  --body "The deployment is complete and smoke tests passed." \\
  --output json
.fi
.SH SEND FROM STDIN
.nf
git log --oneline -5 | teams message send \\
  --team "$TEAM_ID" \\
  --channel "$CHANNEL_ID" \\
  --stdin \\
  --output json
.fi
.SH READ RECENT CHAT METADATA
.nf
CHAT_ID=$(teams chat list --output json | jq -r '.data[0].id')
teams message list --chat "$CHAT_ID" --page-size 10 --output json | \\
  jq '.data[] | {id, createdDateTime, messageType, bodyChars: (.body.content | length)}'
.fi
.PP
This pattern avoids printing raw customer message bodies into logs.
.SH REPLY TO A CHANNEL MESSAGE
.nf
MESSAGE_ID=$(teams message list --team "$TEAM_ID" --channel "$CHANNEL_ID" --output json | jq -r '.data[0].id')
teams message reply \\
  --team "$TEAM_ID" \\
  --channel "$CHANNEL_ID" \\
  --message-id "$MESSAGE_ID" \\
  --body "Acknowledged." \\
  --output json
.fi
.SH FILE SMOKE TEST
.nf
printf 'teams-cli file smoke\\n' | teams file upload \\
  --team "$TEAM_ID" \\
  --channel "$CHANNEL_ID" \\
  --stdin \\
  --name teams-cli-smoke.txt \\
  --output json
.fi
.SH WEBHOOK LISTENER
.nf
teams listen --port 8080
.fi
.PP
Microsoft Graph requires HTTPS notification URLs. Put the local listener behind
an HTTPS tunnel for live subscription testing.
.SH ERROR HANDLING
.nf
if ! output=$(teams message send --chat "$CHAT_ID" --body "Hello" --output json); then
  code=$?
  case "$code" in
    3) teams auth login --device-code ;;
    4) echo "permission denied" >&2 ;;
    6) sleep 30 ;;
    *) echo "$output" >&2 ;;
  esac
fi
.fi
.SH POWERSHELL
.nf
$env:TEAMS_CLI_TENANT_ID = "<tenant-id>"
teams auth login --device-code
teams chat list --output json | ConvertFrom-Json
teams message send --chat $env:TEAMS_TEST_CHAT_ID --body "Windows smoke test" --output json
.fi
.SH SAFETY
Use dedicated test channels for smoke tests. Do not run destructive commands
against production Teams resources unless the target and cleanup plan are
explicit.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR teams (1),
.BR teams-auth (7),
.BR teams-agent-contract (7),
.BR teams-config (5)
